"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-05-paris-2024-olympics-ofili-reflects-on-womens-200m-semi-final-feat\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Favour Ofili has reflected on her impressive performance in the women's 200m at the ongoing 2024 Olympic Games.  Ofili won her heat in blistering fashion, coasting home in a time of 22.24s.  The 21-year-old could not compete in the women's 100m after she was not registered by officials of the Athletics Federation of Nigeria (AFN) and Nigeria Olympic Committee (NOC).  The Delta-State-born athlete said she was determined to showcase her talents at the games.  \\\"Despite the setbacks, I was determined to shine. Mental preparation was key. Regardless of what happened, I was determined to be ready,\\\" Ofili was quoted by making of champions.  \\\"When I step on the track, I aim to cross the line before anyone else. We are all Olympians, and I treat every competitor the same,\\\" she added.  Transfer: Stan Collymore warns Osimhen against Chelsea move  Ancelotti reveals when Mbappe will make his Real Madrid debut  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"